title: Ryan's Genk to face Gent in Europa League

text:
Ryan's Genk to face Gent in Europa League Mat Ryan, right, in action against FC Astra (Getty Images) Australia goalkeeper Mat Ryan's Genk side will take on fellow Belgian outfit Gent in the last 16 of the UEFA Europa League after the draw was made in Nyon. Source: Tweet 
Ryan kept a clean sheet as Genk defeated Romanian outfit FC Astra 1-0 to complete a 3-2 aggregate success in midweek, with the reward a clash with Gent for a place in the quarter-finals. 
The draw also paired Jose Mourinho's Manchester United, who are favourites to win the competition, with Russian Premier League side Rostov. 
United are away in the first leg - initially scheduled for March 9 - with the second leg expected to be played at Old Trafford on March 16. 
The long journey may present a challenge for Mourinho, with the two legs coming either side of the away FA Cup quarter-final against Chelsea scheduled for Monday March 13. 
Two of the main contenders to win the tournament will meet in the tie of the round, with Ligue 1 Lyon doing battle with Serie A heavyweights Roma, Bruno Genesio's men at home for the first leg. 
The draw – made by former Barcelona and Bayern Munich defender Patrick Andersson - was unseeded with no country protection. The official result of the #UELdraw 
— UEFA Europa League (@EuropaLeague) February 24, 2017 
And an all-Bundesliga meeting between Schalke and Borussia Monchengladbach was another exciting tie to be pulled out of the hat. 
LaLiga outfit Celta Vigo play Krasnodar and Greek champions Olympiacos take on last season's Turkish Super Lig winners Besiktas. 
The other ties see APOEL meet two-time finalists Anderlecht, while 1992 winners Ajax are up against Copenhagen.
